{"abstract": "With stock gains at the big banks slowing, cash bonuses may seem relatively more appealing to bank bosses. Investors should keep that in mind, Antony Currie of Reuters Breakingviews writes.", "web_url": "https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2015/01/23/hint-for-investors-in-rise-in-cash-for-wall-st-chiefs-pay/", "snippet": "With stock gains at the big banks slowing, cash bonuses may seem relatively more appealing to bank bosses. Investors should keep that in mind, Antony Currie of Reuters Breakingviews writes.", "lead_paragraph": "Shareholders may want to take a hint from this week\u2019s news on compensation for Wall Street chief executives. JPMorgan Chase is paying a portion of Jamie Dimon\u2019s bonus in cash for the first time since 2011. And Goldman Sachs is bolstering how much cash Lloyd Blankfein gets. Meanwhile, bank stock gains are slowing.", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [{"rank": 0, "subtype": "xlarge", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2015/01/24/business/dbpix-blankfein/dbpix-blankfein-articleLarge.jpg", "height": 400, "width": 600, "subType": "xlarge", "crop_name": "articleLarge", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2015/01/24/business/dbpix-blankfein/dbpix-blankfein-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": 600, "xlargeheight": 400}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "jumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2015/01/24/business/dbpix-blankfein/dbpix-blankfein-jumbo.jpg", "height": 683, "width": 1024, "subType": "jumbo", "crop_name": "jumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "superJumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2015/01/24/business/dbpix-blankfein/dbpix-blankfein-superJumbo.jpg", "height": 1366, "width": 2048, "subType": "superJumbo", "crop_name": "superJumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "thumbnail", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2015/01/24/business/dbpix-blankfein/dbpix-blankfein-thumbStandard.jpg", "he